CEZ AS (CEZ) , the biggest power producer
in the Czech Republic, rose for a second day after neighboring
Germany signaled it will accelerate its exit from nuclear power.  The stock advanced as much as 1.3 percent and traded up 0.9
percent at 888.5 koruna as of 9:50 a.m. in Prague.  German  Chancellor Angela Merkel  said at a press conference
in Berlin April 15 she wants to accelerate the countryâ€™s exit
